== 2024
~~~
{}{img_left}{./images/books/cancer.jpg}{}{250px}{}{}
== The Emperor of All Maladies: A Biography of Cancer
==== Author: Siddhartha Mukherjee
==== Read on: Nov 2024
I think this book needs no introduction due to it's fame. If one wants to know about "Cancer" from scientific, political and historical lens with as much as possible in just one read - this is the must I can recommend.

What we know of cancer today is an amalgamation of hundreds of decades of research (sometimes which might have produced counter-productive results), a lot of politics (it is damn hard to understand how much background happens for an area of research to be this fruitful) and often-times occurring serendipitous events and inspirations from entirely other areas (like statistics, AIDS etc;).

I read the book "Gene" by Siddhartha Mukherjee and that inspired me to pick another dense book and I totally enjoyed reading this one.

There are lots of notes/important points/key takeaways that I can take from this book (even though I am from non-medicine background) and maybe in future I plan to develop some easy-to-read blog posts which can serve as some inspiration for me.

*Tags: * +nonfiction, cancer, medicine, history+
~~~

