== Lying
==== Author: Sam Harris
==== Read on: Aug 2022
Well, whatever information is given by the author, we all know that. But nevertheless, it's important to know the psychology of lying.

The author goes on explaining the different types of lies, different situations where we tend to lie, maintaining secrets, integrity, deception etc;

Eg: Denying to tell the truth is different from telling a different version you won't believe. Suppose you are at place A and when someone asked where you are - You can tell you are not comfortable sharing your location (denying) rather than telling that you are at place B (a different version). Because the moment you lied, you need to remember it, keep track of it and basically are trying to be in 2 different worlds which is not so easy (no one can alter truth and exist in multiple worlds)

In one sentence: Don't lie

